Package: piano
Type: Package
Title: Platform for integrative analysis of omics data
Version: 1.3.5
Date: 2013-11-07
Author@R: c(person("Leif", "Varemo", email = "piano.rpkg@gmail.com",
        role = "aut"), person("Intawat", "Nookaew", email =
        "piano.rpkg@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Author: Leif Varemo <piano.rpkg@gmail.com> and Intawat Nookaew <piano.rpkg@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Leif Varemo <piano.rpkg@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 2.14.0)
Imports: Biobase, gplots, igraph, relations, marray
Suggests: yeast2.db, rsbml, plotrix, limma, affy, plier, affyPLM,
        gtools, biomaRt, snowfall
Description: Piano performs gene set analysis using various statistical methods, from different gene level statistics and a wide range of gene-set collections. Furthermore, the Piano package contains functions for combining the results of multiple runs of gene set analyses.
License: GPL (>=2)
biocViews: Microarray, Preprocessing, QualityControl,
        DifferentialExpression, DataImport, DataRepresentation,
        Visualization
URL: http://www.sysbio.se/piano
